          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.The method of obtaining In-111 and",
                "In-114-m investigated in this paper are the most",
                "effective ones. The isotope In-114-m, free of In-111,",
                "is obtained 35-40 days after irradiation, and In-111",
                "free from In-114-m is obtained by irradiating silver",
                "with alpha particles. When cadmium is irradiated with",
                "protons or deuterons, the In-114-m contents at the end",
                "of irradiation are 0.8 and 3.5% when the proton or",
                "deuteron energy is 22 MeV, however, the yield of In-111",
                "is then three or five times greater than that for",
                "irradiation of silver with approx. 44 MeV alpha",
                "particles."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "STATUS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "status": [
